Minnette Barrett https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minnette_Barrett 0 Minnette Barrett (March 25, 1880 - June 20, 1964) was an American actress. She primarily appeared on stage and in vaudeville, though she also had a few film appearances. She appeared on vaudeville with Joe Jefferson Jr. and Florence Nash.During World War II she led the American Theatre Wing's war bonds drive.
